Plot.
WHAT WE DO IN THE SHADOWS chronicles the adventures of four vampire 
room-mates trying to get by in a modern world that's not always hospitable 
to the undead. Clement and Waititi, creators of the HBO hit series "Flight 
of the Conchords," co-wrote, co-directed, and co-star in this hilarious 
send-up in which an endearingly unhip quartet of friends reveal to us or, 
rather, to the documentary crew that's filming them, the details of their 
daily-make that nightly-routine. Ranging in age from 183 to 8,000, and 
in appearance from adorably youthful to Nosferatu-crusty, they squabble 
over household chores, struggle to keep up with the latest trends in 
technology and fashion, antagonize the local werewolves, cruise clubs 
for lovely ladies, and deal with the rigours of living on a very, very 
strict diet.
